  "prompt": "What are the best resources for studying Sanskrit in English?",
  "response": "Here are some excellent resources for studying Sanskrit in English:\n\nBooks:\n1. \"Complete Sanskrit\" by Michael Coulson\n2. \"Sanskrit: An Introduction to the Classical Language\" by Michael Coulson\n3. \"A Sanskrit Grammar for Students\" by Arthur A. MacDonell\n4. \"Teach Yourself Sanskrit\" by Michael Coulson\n\nOnline Courses:\n1. Spoken Sanskrit Online (spoken-sanskrit.de)\n2. Sanskrit Tutorial by Sanskrit.Today\n3. Coursera courses on Sanskrit language\n4. edX Sanskrit language courses\n\nWebsites:\n1. learnsanskrit.org\n2. sanskrit.inria.fr\n3. sanskritdocuments.org\n\nMobile Apps:\n1. Learn Sanskrit\n2. Sanskrit Basics\n3. Speak Sanskrit\n\nYouTube Channels:\n1. Sanskrit Channel\n2. Samskrita Bharati\n3. Learn Sanskrit Online\n\nAcademic Resources:\n1. Digital Sanskrit Library\n2. University of Cambridge Sanskrit resources\n3. University of Oxford Sanskrit studies program\n\nAdditional Learning Tools:\n1. Sanskrit dictionaries like Monier-Williams\n2. Online translation resources\n3. Sanskrit grammar websites\n\nEach resource offers different strengths, so combining multiple approaches can be most effective.",
